title: Sectional Mock 2 - Quantitative Aptitude
instruction: What value should come in the place of (?) in the following questions.

quiz.text: Find the profit share of B after two years out of total profit when A, B and C invest different amounts in a business for different times. [They don’t withdraw any amount in the investment time period] I. B invested for 13 months and C invested 25% more than the total investment of A. II. Total amount invested by A and B together is Rs.26000 and C investment for 12 months. III. A invests 25% more months than C and C invests Rs.16000. IV. B invests his money for 2 years and gets more money among all three.
options: either I or III is sufficient
I, II, & IV are sufficient
only IV is sufficient
Both II & IV are sufficient
None is sufficient

quiz.text: Find the sum of the present age of C and D. I. Ratio of the present age of A to C is 3:5. After 5 years B’s age will be equal to the present age of C. II. C’s age is the average age of the present age of F and B. D’s present age is the average of the present age of E and F. Age of E is 40 years. III. F’s age is double the present age of A. Sum of the age of A and E is equal to the sum of age of B and D together. IV. Ratio of age D and F is 6:5. The difference between age D and A is 20. D is older than A.
options: Both II & IV are sufficient
Only IV is sufficient
None is sufficient
Either I or III is sufficient
I, II, & IV are sufficient

quiz.text: What is the speed of train Q? I. Speed of train P is 25% more than the speed of train Q. Train P cross 180 m long bridge in 15 sec. II. Train R crosses a bridge of double his length in 20 sec and the ratio of the length of P and Q is 2:3. III. Train P cross train Q in 5 sec when they moving towards each other and train R and train P cross each other when they moving the same direction in 12 sec., IV. Speed of train R is 72 km/hr and the length of train R is 180 m.
options: Both II & IV are sufficient
both I & II are sufficient
Both I & IV are sufficient
Any two is sufficient
None is sufficient

quiz.text: Find the profit or loss percentage of A when he buys a phone and sells it to others. I. A sells the phone to B and B sells the phone to C. C sells the phone to D at 10% profit. II. Profit percentage of A and C is equal. B sells the phone at Rs.14200. III. B makes a profit of 15% when he sells the phone to C. A buys the phone at Rs.12000. IV. Profit amount of A is half of profit amount of C. C buy Rs.2400 more price than the price in which A buy.
options: Both II & I are sufficient
only IV is sufficient
only I is sufficient
either I or III is sufficient
none is sufficient

quiz.text: On Monday, Venu had a ticket on boat E but he couldn’t catch it. He instead boarded on ship C which departed 3 hours later. After how much distance Venu will be able to board on boat E(both ships were travelling upstream)?
options: 216 Km
300 Km
330 Km
270 Km
None of these

quiz.text: On Wednesday, all boats leave for port on a side of the river followed by a gap of 1.5 hour each flowing upstream. Boat A leaves first followed by E, B, D and C respectively. If the other port is 607.75 Km away from 1st end, which ship will reach the other port second?
options: A
B
C
D
None of these

quiz.text: Average speed of A on three days is what percent of average speed of C on Monday and Wednesday only?
options: 74.50 %
62.50 %
70.37 %
72.27 %
None of these

quiz.text: Vipul is travelling on boat D on Monday which was going downstream. He has to travel 414 Km and reach his destination by 8 pm. The boat departed the port at 11 am. The boat kept travelling at the  same speed till 2 pm when on Vipul’s request, the captain agreed to increase the speed. What must be the percentage change in speed of the boat so that Vipul reaches the destination by time?
options: 46.875 %
41.67 %
43.50 %
42.857 %
None of these

quiz.text: What is the average downstream speed of all the boats on Tuesday?
options: 72 kmph
61.6 kmph
60 kmph
64.8 kmph
None of these

quiz.text: A alone complete the work in 48 days and the efficiency of A is 75% of the efficiency of B. If A and B started the work and after 12 days A left the work and then B and C together can complete the remaining work in 10 days, in how many days C alone can complete the work?
options: 54 days
60 days
68 days
72 days
78 days

quiz.text: A box contains x red balls and x – 2 black balls. If the probability of drawing a red ball is 1/4 more than the probability of drawing a black ball, then find the value of x?
options: 3
4
5
6
7

quiz.text: Keerthy invests Rs.(x + 4000) in a simple interest scheme at the rate of 12% per annum for 3 years. After 3 years, Keerthy received the total amount from the SI scheme and invested in a compound interest scheme at the rate of 10% per annum for 2 years. If the total interest received by Keerthy from both schemes is Rs.3228, then find the value of x.
options: Rs.1000
Rs.1200
Rs.1500
Rs.1800
Rs.1400

quiz.text: P and Q can fill the tank in 6 hours and with help of R the tank is filled in 4 hours. P, Q and S together can fill the tank in 9.6 hours. Pipe P, Q and S are opened together for 8 hours and then pipe P and Q are  closed and pipe R is opened. How many hours pipe R and S together will take to fill the remaining tank?
options: 9 hours
6 hours
4 hours
5 hours
8 hours

quiz.text: Shopkeeper mixed two varieties of oil of the price Rs.180 per liter and Rs.144 per liter and the quantity of oil price of Rs.144 double of the oil price of Rs.180. If he sold the mixture for Rs.5616, then find the quantity of oil that cost Rs.180 per liter sold by the shopkeeper?
options: 20 liters
15 liters
18 liters
12 liters
None of these

quiz.text: Four years ago, the ratio of the age of Rani and Vani was 11:7. After 16 years from now, the ratio of their age becomes 4:3. If the present average age of Rani, Vani and Mani is 40 years, then find the present age of Mani.
options: 35 years
40 years
45 years
30 years
55 years

quiz.text: A started the business with the investment of Rs.6000 and B joined the business by investing Rs.8000 after certain months. After 8 months, C joined the business by investing Rs.5000. At the end of the year, the total profit of the business is Rs.16500 and the profit share of A is Rs.9000. Find the time after which month B joined the business?
options: 4
5
6
7
8

quiz.text: The length of train A is 12.5% more than the length of train B. Train A crosses a man in 15 seconds and train B crosses a man in 12 seconds while train B also crosses a 240 m long tunnel in 30 seconds. Then find the speed of train A?
options: 12 m/s
10 m/s
15 m/s
13 m/s
18 m/s

quiz.text: Ratio of the Marked price to the cost price of the laptop is 9:5. The shopkeeper allows two successive discounts of 20% and 25% respectively. If the shopkeeper sold it at a single discount of 35%, he would have gained Rs.180 more. Find the selling price of the laptop at a profit of 30%?
options: Rs.3900
Rs.3600
Rs.3400
Rs.3200
Rs.2600

quiz.text: The downstream speed of the boat is 25% more than the upstream speed of the same boat. If the boat covers 234 km in still water in 13 hours, then find the time taken by the boat to cover 480 km along with the stream?
options: 20 hours
21 hours
25 hours
22 hours
24 hours

930
940

960

What is the ratio of the number of boys in school D in both years to the number of boys in school E in both years together?

10:11
39:44
19:24
